title: Feasibility Study — Lusail Refrigerated Distribution Hub
summary: A 12,000-pallet automated cold-storage and last-mile hub serving Greater Doha
meta: | type: feasibility | ref: FS-2026-031 | client: Qatar Fresh Foods Co. | prepared-by: Gulf Infrastructure Advisory | prepared-for: Investment Committee | date: 2026-06-24 | status: draft | theme: corporate

toc:

section: 1. Executive Summary
text: This study assesses the feasibility of building and operating an automated refrigerated distribution hub in the Lusail Logistics Zone. The facility would consolidate frozen and chilled inventory presently spread across three leased warehouses, cutting outbound transport distance and spoilage while adding third-party logistics (3PL) capacity for the growing Doha grocery and food-service market.

text: On a 10-year horizon the project clears the sponsor's 13% hurdle rate, returns a real internal rate of return of 16.8%, and reaches cumulative break-even in year 6. The base case assumes a phased commissioning with Phase 1 (8,000 pallets) live by Q3 2027 and full automation by Q1 2028.

text: The principal risks are construction cost escalation on refrigeration plant and a slower-than-modelled 3PL occupancy ramp. Both are mitigable, and on the downside scenario the project still returns capital. The recommendation is to proceed to detailed design and a binding EPC tender.

objective: Reduce blended cold-chain cost per pallet-month below 95 QAR | owner: COO | by: 2028-03-31
objective: Achieve 85% utilisation across owned + 3PL pallet positions within 24 months of full commissioning | owner: Commercial Director
scope: In scope — civil works, refrigeration plant, automated storage/retrieval (ASRS), WMS, and fleet electrification. Out of scope — upstream procurement, retail storefronts.

section: 2. Key Metrics
text: The headline indicators below are evaluated against the sponsor's investment policy. Each card reports its target, multi-period trend, or measurement window.

metric: Net Present Value (10y, real) | value: 318 | unit: QAR | trend: up | period: 10 years
metric: Internal Rate of Return | value: 16.8% | target: 13% | trend: up
metric: Discounted Payback | value: 6.1 years | target: 7 years | period: base case
metric: Year-3 EBITDA Margin | value: 31.4% | target: 28% | trend: up
metric: Peak Utilisation (Year 5) | value: 88% | target: 85% | period: stabilised
metric: Cost per Pallet-Month | value: 91 | unit: QAR | target: 95 QAR | trend: down
metric: Carbon Intensity vs. leased baseline | value: -34% | trend: down | period: at full electrification

text: NPV is stated in millions of QAR, real terms, discounted at the 13% hurdle. All currency metrics carry the bare magnitude in value: and the ISO-4217 code in unit: for machine querying.

section: 3. Key Assumptions
text: The model rests on the following assumptions. Each is rated for confidence; low-confidence items are carried into the sensitivity analysis in Section 5.

assumption: Total developed capacity of 12,000 pallet positions across chilled (2-8°C) and frozen (-22°C) chambers | confidence: high
assumption: Phase 1 commissioning of 8,000 positions by 2027-09-30, full automation by 2028-03-31 | confidence: medium
assumption: Blended occupancy ramps 55% (Y1) → 72% (Y2) → 85% (Y3) → 88% (Y5) | confidence: medium
assumption: Owned inventory occupies 60% of positions; 3PL clients take the balance | confidence: medium
assumption: Average storage tariff of 140 QAR per pallet-month for 3PL clients, fixed for 3 years then CPI-indexed | confidence: medium
assumption: Grid electricity at 0.13 QAR/kWh; on-site solar covers 18% of refrigeration load by Year 4 | confidence: low
assumption: Land secured on a 25-year Lusail Logistics Zone ground lease at 38 QAR/m² per year | confidence: high
assumption: Construction inflation of 6% per year applied to the 2026 base estimate | confidence: low
assumption: Corporate tax treatment per Qatar free-zone incentives; no withholding modelled on domestic revenue | confidence: medium

cite: Qatar General Electricity & Water Corp. tariff schedule 2026 | section: Commercial — Industrial
cite: Lusail Logistics Zone ground-lease framework | section: Schedule 2

