section: 5. Sensitivity Analysis
text: The base-case NPV of 318M QAR was stress-tested against the two lowest-confidence assumptions. The project remains value-positive in every modelled scenario.

| Scenario | Change vs. base | NPV (M QAR) | IRR | Verdict |
| Base case | — | 318 | 16.8% | Proceed |
| Capex +15% | construction escalation | 251 | 14.9% | Proceed |
| Occupancy ramp -1 year slower | demand risk | 274 | 15.3% | Proceed |
| Tariff -10% | pricing pressure | 233 | 14.1% | Proceed |
| Combined downside | all three | 168 | 13.4% | Marginal |

risk: Refrigeration plant cost escalation | severity: high | likelihood: medium | mitigation: fixed-price EPC contract with capped escalation clause
risk: 3PL occupancy ramp slower than modelled | severity: high | likelihood: medium | mitigation: pre-let 40% of 3PL positions before commissioning
risk: Grid tariff increase eroding margin | severity: medium | likelihood: medium | mitigation: accelerate on-site solar to 30% of load
risk: ASRS technology integration delay | severity: medium | likelihood: low | mitigation: phased cutover with manual fallback aisles
risk: Free-zone tax incentive withdrawn | severity: high | likelihood: low | mitigation: model sustains positive NPV at standard corporate rate

section: 6. Implementation Roadmap
deadline: EPC tender issued | date: 2026-09-15 | consequence: schedule slip pushes Phase 1 revenue into 2028
deadline: Phase 1 commissioning (8,000 positions) | date: 2027-09-30 | consequence: delayed revenue start, cumulative break-even slips
deadline: Full automation cutover | date: 2028-03-31 | consequence: 3PL service-level commitments at risk

task: Commission independent quantity surveyor cost review | owner: Head of Projects | due: 2026-07-31 | priority: high
task: Secure board approval for ground lease execution | owner: CFO | due: 2026-08-15 | priority: high
task: Pre-let 40% of 3PL pallet positions | owner: Commercial Director | due: 2027-06-30 | priority: medium

section: 7. Recommendation
info: PROCEED to detailed design and a binding EPC tender. The project clears the 13% hurdle in every scenario, returns capital by year 6, and only turns marginal under a combined triple-downside that the mitigations above directly address. | type: success

recommendation: Authorise Phase 1 detailed design (budget 4.2M QAR) and issue the EPC tender by 2026-09-15 | owner: Investment Committee | basis: base-case IRR 16.8% vs. 13% hurdle
condition: Proceed conditional on the independent quantity surveyor confirming the 246M QAR capex within a +/-8% band | owner: CFO

quote: A 13.4% return survives our worst combined case — the question is execution discipline, not viability. | by: Lead Analyst, Gulf Infrastructure Advisory

